comments: Beal (WAS) and Allen (CLE) make incidental contact with each other during the loose ball.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Okoro (CLE) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Harrell (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Garland (CLE) and absorbs the contact.
Allen (CLE) legally contests the driving shot attempt by Dinwiddie (WAS) and any contact is incidental.
Rubio (CLE) holds down Harrell's (WAS) left arm and affects his ability to get to the rebound.
Okoro (CLE) jumps towards the ball to grab the rebound and his momentum carries him into Harrell (WAS).  The contact is incidental.
Allen (CLE) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (WAS) and does not deliver contact as he firms up.
Beal (WAS) makes marginal contact with Osman (CLE) as he releases the pass.
Garland (CLE) makes a legal move during his dribble.
Gafford (WAS) extends his hip towards Mobley (CLE) during the screen but any contact is marginal.
Beal (WAS) is in Stevens' (CLE) path and the two players briefly engage and disengage.
Beal (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball as he falls to the floor and then commits a take foul on Rubio (CLE).
Stevens (CLE) grabs Beal (WAS) with both hands to attempt to commit a take foul.
Mobley (CLE) places his hand on Kuzma (WAS), who is already off-balance, and the contact during the loose ball is marginal.
Mobley (CLE) is whistled for being the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  There is no conclusive video evidence that confirms if Kuzma (WAS) touches the ball last.
Osman (CLE) commits a take foul on Beal (WAS).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the game clock is reset to 00:00.7 and the Cavaliers are given possession at the original spot of the throw-in.
